Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.78,0:53:08.50,English,,0,0,0,,continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation their cultural values.\N{\rChinese}他们的文化价值观。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.74,0:53:12.34,English,,0,0,0,,This is a culture that emphasizes three things.\N{\rChinese}这是一种强调三件事的文化。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.64,0:53:13.92,English,,0,0,0,,First is freedom.\N{\rChinese}首先是自由。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.66,0:53:18.48,English,,0,0,0,,Second is egalitarianism.\N{\rChinese}第二是平等主义。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.22,0:53:24.54,English,,0,0,0,,And the third is self -reliance.\N{\rChinese}第三是自给自足。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.86,0:53:31.16,English,,0,0,0,,So rather than think of the Mongol,\N{\rChinese}于是把蒙古军队想成一个联邦，而不是帝国或组织
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.44,0:53:36.24,English,,0,0,0,,the army as an empire or organization, it's more like a confederation.\N{\rChinese}the army as an empire or organization, it's more like a confederation.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.46,0:53:39.90,English,,0,0,0,,People choose to join this confederation because\N{\rChinese}人们选择加入这个联邦是因为
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.90,0:53:42.88,English,,0,0,0,,of the immense rewards that\N{\rChinese}巨大的奖励
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.88,0:53:45.18,English,,0,0,0,,can be achieved through conquest.\N{\rChinese}可通过征服实现。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.12,0:53:49.00,English,,0,0,0,,So this is a culture that values freedom,\N{\rChinese}于是这是一种重视自由的文化。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.16,0:53:53.44,English,,0,0,0,,egalitarianism, and self -reliance, and therefore it makes great warriors.\N{\rChinese}平等主义，自给自足，因而造就伟大武士。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.64,0:53:57.56,English,,0,0,0,,The problem though\N{\rChinese}问题在于……
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.56,0:54:01.42,English,,0,0,0,,is the cultures they conquer were extremely,\N{\rChinese}被征服的文化极其多样，
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.50,0:54:04.12,English,,0,0,0,,extreme hierarchies.\N{\rChinese}层级极其分明。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.00,0:54:09.72,English,,0,0,0,,Where you have maybe the emperor at the top, a bureaucracy,\N{\rChinese}你可能会把皇帝放在顶端，设有官僚体系。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.18,0:54:13.82,English,,0,0,0,,and then peasantry at the very bottom.\N{\rChinese}并且在最底层是农民。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.90,0:54:17.00,English,,0,0,0,,So the vast majority were peasants.\N{\rChinese}于是大多数都是农民。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.70,0:54:21.90,English,,0,0,0,,Now, I know this is hard for us to understand,\N{\rChinese}现在，我知道这对我们来说很难理解。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.12,0:54:25.20,English,,0,0,0,,but the reason why the Mongols were\N{\rChinese}但蒙古人能征服这些帝国的原因是……
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.20,0:54:27.58,English,,0,0,0,,able to conquer these empires\N{\rChinese}他们能够征服这些帝国的原因是……
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.58,0:54:31.66,English,,0,0,0,,were almost a contempt\N{\rChinese}能征服这些帝国的原因几乎是……
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.18,0:54:34.64,English,,0,0,0,,for these empires.\N{\rChinese}为这些帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.78,0:54:38.02,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense, guys? The Mongols had no respect for these empires.\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗，大家？蒙古人对这些帝国毫不敬重。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.14,0:54:41.22,English,,0,0,0,,They thought they were weak. They thought they were corrupt and\N{\rChinese}他们认为它们弱小，腐败无能。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.22,0:54:42.96,English,,0,0,0,,decadent.\N{\rChinese}黙黙的。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.34,0:54:45.94,English,,0,0,0,,So the Mongols were able to conquer them.\N{\rChinese}于是蒙古人能够征服它们。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.10,0:54:48.98,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? There's a contempt for them.\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗？对它们有一种轻视。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.28,0:54:50.38,English,,0,0,0,,The contempt is this.\N{\rChinese}这就是轻视的含义。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.10,0:54:57.72,English,,0,0,0,,The underlying optimal strategy of the Mongols is a concept\N{\rChinese}蒙古人的基本最优策略是一个在人类历史中从未出现过的概念。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.72,0:54:59.40,English,,0,0,0,,that never existed in human history before.\N{\rChinese}that never existed inhuman history before.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.64,0:55:05.60,English,,0,0,0,,And the concept is this. People are an infinite resource.\N{\rChinese}概念就是这样：人是无限资源。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.84,0:55:15.12,English,,0,0,0,,So throughout most of human history, people were the most valuable resource.\N{\rChinese}于是，在大部分人类历史里，人是最宝贵的资源。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.38,0:55:16.82,English,,0,0,0,,There was not many people around.\N{\rChinese}当时人不多。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.16,0:55:21.00,English,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you had to treat people nicely if you wanted to maximize their productivity.\N{\rChinese}因此，如果想最大化人力产出，你就得好好对待他们。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.64,0:55:25.92,English,,0,0,0,,But where\N{\rChinese}但在何处
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.92,0:55:27.88,English,,0,0,0,,were the Mongols based?\N{\rChinese}蒙古人是从哪里起家的？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.10,0:55:31.36,English,,0,0,0,,They were based in East Asia. They were based in China, basically.\N{\rChinese}他们起源于东亚，基本上是中国。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.66,0:55:33.80,English,,0,0,0,,And in China, because of the empire,\N{\rChinese}在中国，因帝国的存在，
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.12,0:55:36.68,English,,0,0,0,,people were treated like an infinite resource.\N{\rChinese}人们被视作无限资源。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.00,0:55:39.90,English,,0,0,0,,You could massacre them.\N{\rChinese}你可以大肆杀戮他们。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.02,0:55:42.68,English,,0,0,0,,You could send them off in human wave attacks.\N{\rChinese}你可以派他们去人潮攻击。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.30,0:55:46.32,English,,0,0,0,,It didn't matter, because they were an infinite resource.\N{\rChinese}这不重要，因为他们是无限资源。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.68,0:55:50.36,English,,0,0,0,,And this idea never existed before in human history.\N{\rChinese}并且此概念在人类史上从未曾出现。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.58,0:55:54.32,English,,0,0,0,,And in the Western world, this concept is radically revolutionary.\N{\rChinese}在西方世界，此概念彻底革新。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.06,0:55:56.60,English,,0,0,0,,It was unimaginable.\N{\rChinese}其曾是不可思议的。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.70,0:55:58.36,English,,0,0,0,,Like, you could do this.\N{\rChinese}比如，你可以这么做。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.44,0:56:03.38,English,,0,0,0,,continuation continuation Caesar even though he\N{\rChinese}继续，继续，凯撒甚至……
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.38,0:56:05.42,English,,0,0,0,,when\N{\rChinese}当时……
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.42,0:56:10.58,English,,0,0,0,,he conquered Rome he wasn't intent on massacring people why\N{\rChinese}他征服了罗马，他并非要大屠杀人们，为什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.58,0:56:13.26,English,,0,0,0,,because people could be sold as slaves that\N{\rChinese}因为人们可以被卖为奴隶，那是他通过把高卢人卖为奴隶赚大钱的主要方式。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.26,0:56:16.92,English,,0,0,0,,was the main way he made his fortune by selling the Gauls as slaves\N{\rChinese}was the main way he made his fortune by selling the Gauls as slaves
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.92,0:56:20.28,English,,0,0,0,,but if you believe\N{\rChinese}但如果你认为
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.28,0:56:23.52,English,,0,0,0,,that people are an infinite resource then\N{\rChinese}人是无限资源，那么
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.52,0:56:27.04,English,,0,0,0,,you don't want them as slaves okay you want you want to\N{\rChinese}你不想把他们当奴隶，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.04,0:56:31.22,English,,0,0,0,,kill as many people as possible in order to inflict terror okay\N{\rChinese}杀死尽可能多的人以制造恐怖，好的，
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.22,0:56:33.80,English,,0,0,0,,so that that's the issue with the Mongols first of all\N{\rChinese}所以这就是蒙古人的问题，首先是他们的价值体系不够……
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.80,0:56:36.32,English,,0,0,0,,their value system not lend\N{\rChinese}their value system not lend
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.32,0:56:40.98,English,,0,0,0,,itself to governing a hierarchy they didn't know how to\N{\rChinese}自己去治理层级，他们不懂怎么做
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.98,0:56:44.24,English,,0,0,0,,and they didn't want to also much more problematic\N{\rChinese}而且他们也不想再多做
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.24,0:56:46.22,English,,0,0,0,,was their contempt for the\N{\rChinese}他们对中国人的轻视是如此
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.22,0:56:50.50,English,,0,0,0,,local culture okay if you have\N{\rChinese}本地文化若你掌握，
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.50,0:56:54.24,English,,0,0,0,,contempt for local culture you're gonna have problems managing the people\N{\rChinese}若你轻视本地文化，管理人就会有难度，
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.24,0:57:00.02,English,,0,0,0,,so in China during the Yuan Dynasty you can't have an American government you can't have an American government the Chinese there's a class system the Mongols were the top\N{\rChinese}于是元朝时，若有美式政府，必有阶级体系，蒙古人位于顶层
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.02,0:57:05.12,English,,0,0,0,,and the Chinese were the very bottom okay the foreigners were sort of in between\N{\rChinese}并且中国人处于最底层，外来者则介于其间
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.12,0:57:07.52,English,,0,0,0,,and that\N{\rChinese}而已
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.52,0:57:10.66,English,,0,0,0,,just shows you the Mongol contempt for for Chinese people\N{\rChinese}这点正显示蒙古人对中国人的轻视
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.66,0:57:13.42,English,,0,0,0,,and that's why ultimately the Chinese people\N{\rChinese}于是，最终中国人起了反抗蒙古人
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.42,0:57:17.32,English,,0,0,0,,rebelled against the Mongols right now\N{\rChinese}现在，最终蒙古领导层意识到这个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.32,0:57:23.28,English,,0,0,0,,eventually the Mongol leadership would recognize this problem\N{\rChinese}于是，最终中国人起了反抗蒙古人
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.28,0:57:27.38,English,,0,0,0,,and they were trying to adopt a Chinese style bureaucracy\N{\rChinese}他们正试图采用中国式的官僚制度
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.38,0:57:29.50,English,,0,0,0,,but a bureaucracy and\N{\rChinese}但官僚制度与…
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.50,0:57:31.46,English,,0,0,0,,we discussed this comes in contact with the\N{\rChinese}我们讨论过这点与…
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.46,0:57:34.52,English,,0,0,0,,nobility okay nobility the nobility\N{\rChinese}贵族，好吧，贵族，贵族
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.52,0:57:40.08,English,,0,0,0,,is intent on maintaining the Mongolian culture they did not want to assimilate\N{\rChinese}贵族意在保持蒙古文化，他们不想同化
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.08,0:57:45.04,English,,0,0,0,,but the Emperor recognized you have to assimilate if you are to have this empire\N{\rChinese}但皇帝认得，若要有这帝国，必须同化
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.04,0:57:48.48,English,,0,0,0,,and because they couldn't agree the nobility and\N{\rChinese}因为贵族之间无法达成一致，皇帝也未能统一，最终导致了蒙古帝国的崩溃。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.48,0:57:51.96,English,,0,0,0,,the Emperor couldn't agree ultimately it led to\N{\rChinese}蒙古帝国的崩溃。
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.96,0:57:55.36,English,,0,0,0,,the collapse of the Mongol Empire okay\N{\rChinese}the collapse of the Mongol Empire okay
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.70,0:57:59.66,English,,0,0,0,,all right so\N{\rChinese}好的，接下来
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.66,0:58:04.76,English,,0,0,0,,that's the history of the Mongols any comments any questions\N{\rChinese}这就是蒙古人的历史，大家有评论吗？有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.04,0:58:10.78,English,,0,0,0,,I know Doug is\N{\rChinese}我知道道格是
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.78,0:58:13.94,English,,0,0,0,,but\N{\rChinese}但
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.94,0:58:17.30,English,,0,0,0,,but but but did you want to make a comment\N{\rChinese}但但但你想发个评论吗
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.30,0:58:20.72,English,,0,0,0,,because I know you said the Mongols quite in\N{\rChinese}因为我知道你说过蒙古人很…
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.72,0:58:24.20,English,,0,0,0,,detail I'm kind of scared this is on YouTube\N{\rChinese}细节，我有点怕这在YouTube上出现
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.16,0:58:29.34,English,,0,0,0,,okay all right yeah all right so yeah it's fine\N{\rChinese}好，没问题，好的，好的，没问题，好的
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.20,0:58:38.48,English,,0,0,0,,okay any questions guys like I know this is a lot to take in\N{\rChinese}好，大家有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.48,0:58:43.40,English,,0,0,0,,so you know ask questions tell me\N{\rChinese}所以你知道，问问题告诉我
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.40,0:58:51.94,English,,0,0,0,,where areas you are confused by okay\N{\rChinese}在哪些地方你感到困惑，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.46,0:59:07.42,English,,0,0,0,,continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation continuation!!!!!\N{\rChinese}继续，继续，继续，继续，继续，继续，继续，继续，继续！
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.20,0:59:26.60,English,,0,0,0,,continuation!\N{\rChinese}继续！
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.60,0:59:29.60,English,,0,0,0,,continuation! Okay,\N{\rChinese}继续！好的，
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.60,0:59:30.74,English,,0,0,0,,alright, so\N{\rChinese}好的，
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.74,0:59:36.48,English,,0,0,0,,the Vikings\N{\rChinese}维京人
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.48,0:59:39.98,English,,0,0,0,,and the Mongols all come from a Proto -Indo -European culture.\N{\rChinese}和蒙古人都来自原始-印欧文化。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.32,0:59:43.06,English,,0,0,0,,What we know about culture is that it's very fluid,\N{\rChinese}我们对文化的了解是它非常流动。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.16,0:59:45.98,English,,0,0,0,,and it will change over time, and\N{\rChinese}并且会随时间变化，且
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.98,0:59:48.66,English,,0,0,0,,it will adapt itself to the local cultures, okay?\N{\rChinese}它会适应当地文化，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.38,0:59:53.64,English,,0,0,0,,And so the Vikings were in Europe.\N{\rChinese}于是维京人就出现在欧洲。
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.62,0:59:59.68,English,,0,0,0,,And the Mongols are near China, okay?\N{\rChinese}蒙古人靠近中国，好的？
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.78,1:00:04.72,English,,0,0,0,,And I have to say,\N{\rChinese}我得说，
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.06,1:00:06.30,English,,0,0,0,,like,\N{\rChinese}像，
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.40,1:00:11.06,English,,0,0,0,,I think if I wanted to be a Viking or a Mongol,\N{\rChinese}我想如果我想成为维京人或蒙古人，
Dialogue: 0,1:00:11.20,1:00:14.40,English,,0,0,0,,I prefer to be a Viking, okay? And\N{\rChinese}我更喜欢成为维京人，好吗？而且
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.40,1:00:16.64,English,,0,0,0,,the reason why is the\N{\rChinese}原因是
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.64,1:00:18.36,English,,0,0,0,,Vikings never really\N{\rChinese}维京人从未真正
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.36,1:00:22.66,English,,0,0,0,,adopted a belief\N{\rChinese}采用过一种信念
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.66,1:00:24.46,English,,0,0,0,,that people were an infinite resource.\N{\rChinese}人是无限资源的观念
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.66,1:00:26.60,English,,0,0,0,,They couldn't. Because Europe was very...\N{\rChinese}他们做不到。因为欧洲很…
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.62,1:00:30.08,English,,0,0,0,,very poor. And the Vikings, regardless, even\N{\rChinese}很贫穷。无论如何，维京人，虽然他们很残暴，却仍然尊敬对手。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.08,1:00:33.28,English,,0,0,0,,though they were brutal, they still had respect for their opponents.\N{\rChinese}though they were brutal, they still had respect for their opponents.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.60,1:00:36.94,English,,0,0,0,,They never developed a contempt for their opponents.\N{\rChinese}他们从未形成对手的敬意。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.08,1:00:40.82,English,,0,0,0,,They were surrounded by the Byzantines, the Muslims, and the Europeans.\N{\rChinese}他们被拜占庭人、穆斯林人和欧洲人包围。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.24,1:00:45.80,English,,0,0,0,,And these were great warriors. So the Vikings felt they had a lot to learn from these cultures.\N{\rChinese}这些人都是伟大的战士。于是维京人觉得可以从这些文化中学到很多东西。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.02,1:00:51.70,English,,0,0,0,,And in fact, ultimately, the Vikings will assimilate themselves into these cultures in different environments,\N{\rChinese}实际上，最终，维京人会在不同环境中将自己同化到这些文化中，
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.82,1:00:53.10,English,,0,0,0,,okay? So...\N{\rChinese}好吧？所以……
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.00,1:00:58.48,English,,0,0,0,,Um... Um... The Mongols are different, though.\N{\rChinese}嗯……嗯……蒙古人则不同，虽然如此。
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.52,1:01:00.56,English,,0,0,0,,The Mongols are based in East Asia.\N{\rChinese}蒙古人位于东亚。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.00,1:01:05.40,English,,0,0,0,,And they did ultimately adopt a belief that people are an infinite resource.\N{\rChinese}他们最终形成了人是无限资源的信念。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.74,1:01:08.98,English,,0,0,0,,And they had tremendous contempt for Chinese culture, okay?\N{\rChinese}他们对中国文化有极大的敬意，好的？
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.18,1:01:12.70,English,,0,0,0,,And that changes you as a person.\N{\rChinese}并且这会让你成为一个人改变。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.76,1:01:16.20,English,,0,0,0,,When you believe that people are an infinite resource,\N{\rChinese}当你相信人是无限资源时，
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.38,1:01:18.92,English,,0,0,0,,and you are contemptuous of other cultures,\N{\rChinese}并且你对其他文化抱有敬意。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.54,1:01:21.84,English,,0,0,0,,it also, in a way,\N{\rChinese}它也在某种程度上，让你对自己产生敬意。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.84,1:01:26.20,English,,0,0,0,,makes you contemptuous of yourself, if that makes any sense.\N{\rChinese}如果这有意义的话，它会让你对自己产生敬意。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.84,1:01:28.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Um...\N{\rChinese}好的？嗯…
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.22,1:01:29.84,English,,0,0,0,,And so, ultimately,\N{\rChinese}于是，最终，
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.04,1:01:33.62,English,,0,0,0,,that's why the Mongols were not able to...\N{\rChinese}这就是蒙古人未能……的原因
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.88,1:01:36.16,English,,0,0,0,,Even though they had tremendous wealth,\N{\rChinese}即便他们拥有巨大的财富，
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.36,1:01:40.94,English,,0,0,0,,they didn't really produce cultural monuments.\N{\rChinese}他们确实没有留下文化纪念物。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.48,1:01:43.04,English,,0,0,0,,We don't have...\N{\rChinese}我们没有……
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.04,1:01:45.56,English,,0,0,0,,Like the Vikings, I mean, as I mentioned,\N{\rChinese}就像维京人一样，我是说，正如我所提到的。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.76,1:01:48.34,English,,0,0,0,,the Vikings were fundamental development of Western civilization.\N{\rChinese}维京人是西方文明的根本发展。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.78,1:01:51.06,English,,0,0,0,,The Mongols were not fundamental development of any civilization.\N{\rChinese}蒙古人不是任何文明的根本发展。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.58,1:01:54.78,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, they caused a lot of havoc, and they were great conquerors.\N{\rChinese}我说的是，他们造成了大量混乱，却是伟大的征服者。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.88,1:01:56.60,English,,0,0,0,,But they didn't leave a rich culture.\N{\rChinese}但他们没有留下丰富的文化。
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.60,1:01:58.34,English,,0,0,0,,They didn't leave a cultural legacy. So...\N{\rChinese}他们没有留下文化遗产。所以……
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.34,1:02:01.14,English,,0,0,0,,And I think it has to do with the belief that\N{\rChinese}我认为这与信念有关。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.14,1:02:03.26,English,,0,0,0,,people are an infinite resource.\N{\rChinese}人是无限的资源。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.68,1:02:05.06,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Um...\N{\rChinese}好？呃……
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.12,1:02:08.48,English,,0,0,0,,So, I would much prefer to be a Viking.\N{\rChinese}所以，我更愿意成为一名维京人。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.58,1:02:12.70,English,,0,0,0,,I would much prefer to be enslaved by a Viking than a Mongol.\N{\rChinese}我更愿意被维京人奴役而不是被蒙古人奴役。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.94,1:02:15.30,English,,0,0,0,,Like, if I were a slave,\N{\rChinese}比如说，如果我是一名奴隶，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.44,1:02:19.66,English,,0,0,0,,I would much rather be a slave to a Viking than a Mongol.\N{\rChinese}我更愿意成为维京人的奴隶而不是蒙古人的。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.84,1:02:22.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? If I were a slave to a Viking,\N{\rChinese}好？如果我是一名维京人的奴隶，
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.30,1:02:24.80,English,,0,0,0,,the Vikings would at least become my friend.\N{\rChinese}维京人至少会成为我的朋友。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.92,1:02:26.58,English,,0,0,0,,They'd be like, hey, tell me about your culture.\N{\rChinese}他们会说：来，跟我说说你的文化。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.60,1:02:29.12,English,,0,0,0,,Are there any stories that you can tell us?\N{\rChinese}你能给我们讲点故事吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.52,1:02:33.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And if you're a great storyteller, then they would make you...\N{\rChinese}好的？如果你是个好故事家，他们就会把你当成…
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.90,1:02:36.64,English,,0,0,0,,Um... They would treat you very nicely, because\N{\rChinese}嗯……他们会很亲切地对待你，因为…
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.64,1:02:38.86,English,,0,0,0,,you're helping them learn more about your culture.\N{\rChinese}你正在帮助他们了解更多关于你的文化。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.96,1:02:41.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The Mongols had absolutely no interest in other cultures.\N{\rChinese}好？蒙古人对其他文化完全没有兴趣。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.00,1:02:45.70,English,,0,0,0,,They were interested in conquering and exploiting other people.\N{\rChinese}他们热衷征服并剥削他人。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.10,1:02:47.80,English,,0,0,0,,All right? I could be wrong. All right?\N{\rChinese}好吧？我也许错了。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.92,1:02:50.46,English,,0,0,0,,And I'm probably making these crass generalizations.\N{\rChinese}我大概在做些粗糙的概括。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.22,1:02:53.76,English,,0,0,0,,But I believe with the Vikings,\N{\rChinese}但我认为与维京人一样。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.88,1:02:56.36,English,,0,0,0,,there's a general curiosity about the world that comes from...\N{\rChinese}有一种来自……的对世界的普遍好奇心。
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.60,1:03:01.04,English,,0,0,0,,And respect of other cultures. Whereas the Mongols were not curious about the world.\N{\rChinese}而蒙古人对世界并不感到好奇。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.16,1:03:02.98,English,,0,0,0,,They were intent on conquest.\N{\rChinese}他们专注征服。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.44,1:03:05.82,English,,0,0,0,,And enslaving other people and exploiting other people.\N{\rChinese}并奴役他人并剥削他人。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.28,1:03:10.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They were predators. And again, that could be my prejudice.\N{\rChinese}好的？他们是掠夺者。再说一次，这也许是我的偏见。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.66,1:03:13.32,English,,0,0,0,,But based on my readings so far,\N{\rChinese}但根据我目前的阅读，
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.52,1:03:16.66,English,,0,0,0,,that would be my belief.\N{\rChinese}那就是我的信念。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.84,1:03:20.72,English,,0,0,0,,But please change my mind. Sounds good.\N{\rChinese}请改改我的想法。听起来不错。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.76,1:03:22.62,English,,0,0,0,,Sounds good. Okay. All right.\N{\rChinese}听起来不错。好的。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.66,1:03:24.70,English,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the question. Okay. Great question.\N{\rChinese}谢谢提问。好的。很棒的问题。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.94,1:03:27.50,English,,0,0,0,,Any other questions? Okay.\N{\rChinese}还有别的问题吗？好的。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.06,1:03:32.06,English,,0,0,0,,So you mentioned that in the Mongols,\N{\rChinese}你提到蒙古人时，
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.16,1:03:33.56,English,,0,0,0,,they don't have a lot of culture.\N{\rChinese}他们的文化不多。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.36,1:03:37.02,English,,0,0,0,,Or... Sorry.\N{\rChinese}或者……抱歉。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.16,1:03:38.38,English,,0,0,0,,Sorry. So population.\N{\rChinese}抱歉。说说人口。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.64,1:03:43.08,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the Mongol population is loosely defined.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以蒙古人的人口大致可定义。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.92,1:03:45.64,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Do you understand?\N{\rChinese}好的？你明白了吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.80,1:03:49.42,English,,0,0,0,,It's hard to say who's Mongol and who's not Mongol.\N{\rChinese}很难说谁是蒙古人，谁不是蒙古人。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.56,1:03:52.48,English,,0,0,0,,Because that entire area has a similar culture.\N{\rChinese}因为那整个地区有相似的文化。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.72,1:03:55.72,English,,0,0,0,,And it's very hard to figure out where the borders are.\N{\rChinese}而且很难确定边界在哪里。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.86,1:03:58.06,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So you mentioned that.\N{\rChinese}好？所以你提到了这一点。
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.06,1:04:00.34,English,,0,0,0,,So you mentioned that people don't have a lot of population.\N{\rChinese}所以你提到人们人口不多。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.74,1:04:02.62,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah. But why would they believe that\N{\rChinese}是的。但他们为什么会认为人是无限资源？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.62,1:04:08.08,English,,0,0,0,,people are infinite resources?\N{\rChinese}people are infinite resources?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.14,1:04:09.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Great question. Okay. Yeah. So you're right.\N{\rChinese}好的。很好的问题。好的。是的。你说得对。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.00,1:04:13.58,English,,0,0,0,,So the Mongols are a low population.\N{\rChinese}蒙古人是人口稀少的。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.18,1:04:16.56,English,,0,0,0,,So why would they believe that people are infinite resources?\N{\rChinese}他们为什么会认为人是无限资源？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.90,1:04:21.10,English,,0,0,0,,And the answer is because they are always in contact with China.\N{\rChinese}答案是因为他们一直与中国接触。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.40,1:04:25.56,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the Mongols were always in contact with China.\N{\rChinese}好的？蒙古人一直与中国接触。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.66,1:04:29.72,English,,0,0,0,,And as... And as I mentioned, the interaction happens in three ways.\N{\rChinese}而且正如我所说，互动以三种方式发生。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:29.88,1:04:35.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The Mongols are working as either mercenaries for dynasties in China.\N{\rChinese}好的？蒙古人要么是为中国朝代雇佣军，要么是做贸易。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.38,1:04:37.08,English,,0,0,0,,Or they are trading.\N{\rChinese}好的？或者他们在掠夺和掠夺。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.48,1:04:40.04,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Or they're raiding and pillaging.\N{\rChinese}好的？或者他们在掠夺和掠夺。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.12,1:04:44.64,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So for centuries, there's been contact between China and the Mongols.\N{\rChinese}好的？于是几个世纪以来，中国和蒙古人一直有接触。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.78,1:04:49.14,English,,0,0,0,,So where did the Mongols learn the idea that people are infinite resources?\N{\rChinese}那么蒙古人是从哪里学到人是无限资源的观念的？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.46,1:04:50.70,English,,0,0,0,,Well, they learned it from China.\N{\rChinese}嗯，就是从中国学来的。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.98,1:04:53.34,English,,0,0,0,,And why did they learn it from China?\N{\rChinese}为什么他们从中国学到这个？
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.48,1:04:56.16,English,,0,0,0,,Because Chinese warfare was also...\N{\rChinese}因为中国的战争也……
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.80,1:04:59.56,English,,0,0,0,,Predicated on the belief that people were an infinite resource.\N{\rChinese}基于人是无限资源的信念。
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.86,1:05:04.12,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? So basically, the entire idea of warfare in China is,\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗？所以，基本上，中国的战争观念是，
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.22,1:05:05.60,English,,0,0,0,,I organize this peasant army.\N{\rChinese}我组织这支农民军队。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.74,1:05:07.20,English,,0,0,0,,I throw it at my opponent.\N{\rChinese}我把它投向我的对手。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.42,1:05:09.96,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And if my entire army dies, guess what?\N{\rChinese}好的？如果我的全军全死，猜猜会怎样？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.12,1:05:12.78,English,,0,0,0,,I'll just go and I'll raise another peasant army and throw it at my opponent again.\N{\rChinese}我就去再组一支农民军，再投向敌人。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.34,1:05:15.90,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? It's like human wafer tax.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就像人力税一样。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.80,1:05:18.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? We call this human wafer tax.\N{\rChinese}好？我们把它叫做人力税。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.28,1:05:19.92,English,,0,0,0,,This was pioneered in China.\N{\rChinese}这在中国先行一步。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.06,1:05:22.96,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And the Mongols just took it and used it everywhere else.\N{\rChinese}蒙古人把它拿来，随处使用。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.02,1:05:27.54,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So if you're the Mongols, and you're fighting this enemy,\N{\rChinese}对吧？如果你是蒙古人，正在和敌人作战，他们把农民抛向你，你把他们全杀掉，但没人在意，因为大约一个月后，又有一支农民军来袭击你。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.76,1:05:30.60,English,,0,0,0,,and they're just throwing these peasants at you, and you're killing them all, but\N{\rChinese}对吧？如果你是蒙古人，正在和敌人作战，他们把农民抛向你，你把他们全杀掉，但没人在意，因为大约一个月后，又有一支农民军来袭击你。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.60,1:05:35.34,English,,0,0,0,,no one cares, because then, like, a month later, another peasant army comes at you.\N{\rChinese}对吧？如果你是蒙古人，正在和敌人作战，他们把农民抛向你，你把他们全杀掉，但没人在意，因为大约一个月后，又有一支农民军来袭击你。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.40,1:05:38.96,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? You quickly adopt the idea that people are an infinite resource.\N{\rChinese}好？你很快就接受了人是无限资源的想法。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.76,1:05:42.20,English,,0,0,0,,Right? Does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}对吧？这样说合理吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.84,1:05:46.04,English,,0,0,0,,I think they were also pretty loose.\N{\rChinese}我觉得他们也很随意。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.88,1:05:50.72,English,,0,0,0,,Those were not regular. But they were pretty loose in terms of,\N{\rChinese}那时并不规律。但在谁能成为蒙古人方面相当自由。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.74,1:05:52.36,English,,0,0,0,,like, who could be a Mongol or not.\N{\rChinese}是的。是的。于是他们就能吸收不同的人口。
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.40,1:05:58.40,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Yeah. And so they could absorb different populations. Yeah.\N{\rChinese}是的。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.62,1:06:09.42,English,,0,0,0,,That's right. Yeah. That's right.\N{\rChinese}对的。嗯。对的。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.54,1:06:12.22,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The Mongols were a very open society.\N{\rChinese}嗯。蒙古人是个非常开放的社会。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.52,1:06:15.46,English,,0,0,0,,Like, if you had a benefit to the society, and so,\N{\rChinese}比如说，如果你能为社会带来好处，
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.48,1:06:20.74,English,,0,0,0,,for example, if you're a Chinese teacher or a Chinese scholar or a Chinese engineer or a Chinese merchant,\N{\rChinese}例如，如果你是中国老师、学者、工程师或商人，他们会很快把你吸收进来。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.88,1:06:22.34,English,,0,0,0,,they would quickly assimilate you.\N{\rChinese}他们随后会把其他人全部杀掉。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.44,1:06:25.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And then they would kill everyone else.\N{\rChinese}Okay? And then they would kill everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.72,1:06:28.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So they were a pretty open society.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以他们是个相当开放的社会。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.88,1:06:30.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}好的？这样说有道理吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:06:31.00,1:06:32.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Great.\N{\rChinese}好的。很好。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.30,1:06:39.08,English,,0,0,0,,Any more questions? Yes.\N{\rChinese}还有问题吗？有。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.02,1:06:50.78,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. Great.\N{\rChinese}好的。很好。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.86,1:06:53.42,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. All right. So let's talk about mythology.\N{\rChinese}好的。好了。现在我们来聊聊神话。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.86,1:06:56.26,English,,0,0,0,,All right. So again, if you actually study mythology,\N{\rChinese}好的。再说一次，如果你真正研究神话，你会发现有一种结构在许多不同文化中非常相似。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.30,1:06:58.86,English,,0,0,0,,what you recognize is\N{\rChinese}好的。再说一次，如果你真正研究神话，你会发现有一种结构在许多不同文化中非常相似。
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.56,1:07:03.66,English,,0,0,0,,there's a structure that's very similar across many different cultures.\N{\rChinese}好的。再说一次，如果你真正研究神话，你会发现有一种结构在许多不同文化中非常相似。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.96,1:07:05.46,English,,0,0,0,,Right? So if you look at Greek,\N{\rChinese}对吧？所以如果你看希腊语，
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.02,1:07:09.12,English,,0,0,0,,if you look at Roman, Norse,\N{\rChinese}如果你看罗马语、北欧语，
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.36,1:07:13.74,English,,0,0,0,,Mongolian, okay, I could go on and on and on.\N{\rChinese}蒙古语，好的，我可以接着说下去。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.08,1:07:19.70,English,,0,0,0,,There is a very similar structure, even though the characters might be different.\N{\rChinese}有一种非常相似的结构，虽然角色可能不同。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.76,1:07:21.92,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But it's a mythology that\N{\rChinese}好的？但这是一种神话，
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.92,1:07:25.00,English,,0,0,0,,celebrates violence and individualism.\N{\rChinese}它赞美暴力与个人主义。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.18,1:07:28.84,English,,0,0,0,,So you can see that there's an individualism as a way to make the world, okay?\N{\rChinese}所以你可以看到，个体主义是一种让世界运转的方式，好的？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.90,1:07:31.34,English,,0,0,0,,So you can see that there's an individualism It's about strength, individualism, violence.\N{\rChinese}所以你可以看到，个体主义是关于力量、个体主义、暴力的。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:32.20,1:07:33.86,English,,0,0,0,,So why is that the case?\N{\rChinese}那为什么会是这样呢？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.96,1:07:36.58,English,,0,0,0,,And it's about culture, cultural values.\N{\rChinese}它关于文化，文化价值。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.56,1:07:41.48,English,,0,0,0,,So as I discussed in this class,\N{\rChinese}正如我在本课中所说，
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.94,1:07:46.02,English,,0,0,0,,cultural values are the most persistent part of who you are.\N{\rChinese}文化价值是你身份中最持久的部分。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.20,1:07:48.38,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Because it's part of your subconscious, okay?\N{\rChinese}为什么？因为它是你潜意识的一部分，好的？
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.48,1:07:51.96,English,,0,0,0,,There's a conscious you and there's a subconscious.\N{\rChinese}有意识的你和潜意识的你。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.32,1:07:57.60,English,,0,0,0,,And ultimately, you are your subconscious.\N{\rChinese}最终，你就是你的潜意识。
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.92,1:08:02.60,English,,0,0,0,,And subconscious is composed of your cultural values.\N{\rChinese}潜意识由你的文化价值构成。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:03.08,1:08:05.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? This is the essence of who you are.\N{\rChinese}好了？这就是你身份的精髓。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.70,1:08:08.52,English,,0,0,0,,So even though the Proto -Indo -Europeans,\N{\rChinese}于是即使原始印欧人，
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.52,1:08:12.02,English,,0,0,0,,they were going into different environments and they were assimilating themselves into different environments\N{\rChinese}他们进入不同的环境，并且他们自己也在不同环境中融合
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.02,1:08:13.60,English,,0,0,0,,and they look physically different,\N{\rChinese}他们看起来身体上不同
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.06,1:08:19.10,English,,0,0,0,,culturally, subconsciously, they shared a similar value system.\N{\rChinese}在文化上，潜意识里他们共享相似的价值体系
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.40,1:08:21.06,English,,0,0,0,,And this value system will then\N{\rChinese}而这个价值体系随后
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.06,1:08:24.80,English,,0,0,0,,go on to inform the way they perceive the world, their worldview.\N{\rChinese}继续影响他们感知世界的方式，即他们的世界观。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.32,1:08:26.88,English,,0,0,0,,And this worldview will then\N{\rChinese}而这个世界观随后
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.88,1:08:30.12,English,,0,0,0,,manifest itself through mythology,\N{\rChinese}通过神话显现，随后成为文学。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.40,1:08:32.06,English,,0,0,0,,which will eventually become literature.\N{\rChinese}好的？这样说通吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.28,1:08:35.24,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}Okay? Does thatmake sense?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.46,1:08:36.98,English,,0,0,0,,So they might have changed clothes,\N{\rChinese}于是他们可能换了衣服，又可能换了发色，但灵魂仍是原始-印欧-语系。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.96,1:08:41.06,English,,0,0,0,,they might have changed their hair color, but\N{\rChinese}于是他们可能换了衣服，又可能换了发色，但灵魂仍是原始-印欧-语系。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.06,1:08:44.62,English,,0,0,0,,their soul was still Proto -Indo -European.\N{\rChinese}于是他们可能换了衣服，又可能换了发色，但灵魂仍是原始-印欧-语系。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.00,1:08:47.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And the same is also true for language.\N{\rChinese}好的？同样的情况也适用于语言。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.14,1:08:51.46,English,,0,0,0,,And that's why so\N{\rChinese}这就是为什么……
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.46,1:08:55.02,English,,0,0,0,,many words repeat themselves in different languages.\N{\rChinese}许多词在不同语言里会重复出现。
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.32,1:08:58.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? All right?\N{\rChinese}好的？行吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.02,1:09:00.46,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? Okay.\N{\rChinese}那有道理吗？好的。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.92,1:09:02.96,English,,0,0,0,,Great. Any more questions?\N{\rChinese}太好了。还有别的问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.10,1:09:08.76,English,,0,0,0,,I don't want to be found. We'll leave the cameras up.\N{\rChinese}我不想被发现。我们把摄像机放好。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.80,1:09:10.16,English,,0,0,0,,We don't want to be found. Okay. All right. Okay.\N{\rChinese}我们不想被发现。好的。行。好的。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.20,1:09:13.10,English,,0,0,0,,Great. So next class, we will go back to Europe.\N{\rChinese}太好了。下节课，我们回到欧洲。
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.16,1:09:16.84,English,,0,0,0,,We will do the Crusades, which will then take us to the Renaissance\N{\rChinese}我们将进行十字军，随后进入文艺复兴与宗教改革，再到南方革命。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.52,1:09:20.44,English,,0,0,0,,and the Reformation and the Southern Revolution. Okay?\N{\rChinese}and the Reformation and theSouthern Revolution. Okay?
